# Missing Access Control in _Settlement_init and()  _Settlement_handler_init() Function

# Lines of code

https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-08-chakra/blob/d0d45ae1d26ca1b87034e67180fac07ce9642fd9/solidity/settlement/contracts/BaseSettlement.sol#L54
https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-08-chakra/blob/d0d45ae1d26ca1b87034e67180fac07ce9642fd9/solidity/handler/contracts/BaseSettlementHandler.sol#L113


# Vulnerability details

### Description:

The `_Settlement_init` function is public and lacks access control, allowing any user to initialize or reinitialize critical contract parameters, including owner assignment and manager roles.


## Code 
```
# BaseSettlement.sol#L54

function _Settlement_init(
      ...
    ) public {//@audit - issue 
        __Ownable_init(_owner);
        __UUPSUpgradeable_init();
        _grantRole(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, _owner); //@audit - issue 

        for (uint256 i = 0; i < _managers.length; i++) {
            _grantRole(MANAGER_ROLE, _managers[i]);
        }

        chain_id = _chain_id;
        contract_chain_name = _chain_name;
        required_validators = _required_validators;
        signature_verifier = ISettlementSignatureVerifier(_signature_verifier);
    }

# BaseSettlementHandler.sol#L113

   function _Settlement_handler_init(
      ...
    ) public { //@audit - issue 
        __Ownable_init(_owner);
        __UUPSUpgradeable_init();
        settlement = ISettlement(_settlement);
        verifier = ISettlementSignatureVerifier(_verifier);
        mode = _mode;
        token = _token;
        chain = _chain;
    }
```

### Impact:

- **Unauthorized owner assignment**
- **Manager role manipulation**
- **Critical parameter changes** (`chain_id`, `required_validators`, `signature_verifier`)



## Tools Used

Manual review :) 

### Recommendation:

* Add an access control modifier like `onlyOwner` or a role-based restriction.



