# `initializeAlphaIndices` uses the wrong modifier and correction for this risks certain protocol functionalities being unavailable.

# Lines of code

https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/279b2887e3d38bc219a05d332cbcb0655b2dc644/contracts/EntropyGenerator/EntropyGenerator.sol#L206
https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/279b2887e3d38bc219a05d332cbcb0655b2dc644/contracts/TraitForgeNft/TraitForgeNft.sol#L353


# Vulnerability details

### Impact

TraitForgeNft.sol doesn't deploy EntropyGenerator.sol and as such is not the owner. Therefore the owner protected functions in EntropyGenerator.sol cannot be directly accessed. Transferring ownership to it however, risks that the ability to pause EntropyGenerator, and set a new allowedCaller will be lost indefinitely.

### Proof of Concept

1. Context

This relies on a bit of speculation.

Important properties of EntropyGenerator.sol to be aware of for this issue.

It's pausable, has an owner and also implements an `onlyAllowedCaller`

```solidity
contract EntropyGenerator is IEntropyGenerator, Ownable, Pausable {
```

```solidity
  modifier onlyAllowedCaller() {
    require(msg.sender == allowedCaller, 'Caller is not allowed');
    _;
  }
```

The allowedCaller can be set, updated or changed by the owner who is the deployer of the contract.

```solidity
  function setAllowedCaller(address _allowedCaller) external onlyOwner {
    allowedCaller = _allowedCaller;
    emit AllowedCallerUpdated(_allowedCaller); // Emit an event for this update.
  }
```
And from the constructor, we discover that the allowedCaller is initially set to the TraitForgeNFT contract.
```solidity
  constructor(address _traitForgetNft) {
    allowedCaller = _traitForgetNft;
    initializeAlphaIndices();
  }
```
And to further cement this, the `onlyAllowedCaller` is used in the `getNextEntropy` function.
```solidity
  function getNextEntropy() public onlyAllowedCaller returns (uint256) {
//...
    return entropy;
  }
```
And in TraitForgeNFT.sol, we can see that the function is called while minting.
```solidity
  function _mintInternal(address to, uint256 mintPrice) internal {
//...
    uint256 entropyValue = entropyGenerator.getNextEntropy();
//...
  }
```

2. Bug Location

In EntropyGenerator.sol, the `initializeAlphaIndices` should be callable by the owner. And since the contract uses [Ownable 4.9.3](https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/279b2887e3d38bc219a05d332cbcb0655b2dc644/package.json#L19) which [sets the deployer as the](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/fd81a96f01cc42ef1c9a5399364968d0e07e9e90/contracts/access/Ownable.sol#L28-L31) owner.

```solidity
  function initializeAlphaIndices() public whenNotPaused onlyOwner {
//...
  }
```

But when we look at TraitForgeNFT.sol, there's no function to deploy EntropyGenerator.sol, its only [set](https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/279b2887e3d38bc219a05d332cbcb0655b2dc644/contracts/TraitForgeNft/TraitForgeNft.sol#L82-L88). So it can be directly inferred that TraitForgeNFT.sol doesn't own EntropyGenerator.sol.

3. Final Effect

This however poses a problem, because when minting, the `incrementGeneration` function is called in the [`_mintInternal`](https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/279b2887e3d38bc219a05d332cbcb0655b2dc644/contracts/TraitForgeNft/TraitForgeNft.sol#L282) and [`_mintNewEntity`](https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/279b2887e3d38bc219a05d332cbcb0655b2dc644/contracts/TraitForgeNft/TraitForgeNft.sol#L334). This function attempts to call `initializeAlphaIndices` in EntropyGenerator.sol and as has been established, can only be called by the owner, which is not TraitForgeNFT.sol.

```solidity
  function _incrementGeneration() private {
//...
    entropyGenerator.initializeAlphaIndices();
    emit GenerationIncremented(currentGeneration);
  }
```

Now this can be fixed, by calling the [`transferOwnership`](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/fd81a96f01cc42ef1c9a5399364968d0e07e9e90/contracts/access/Ownable.sol#L69) function and transferring ownership to TraitForgeNft.sol.

```solidity
    function transferOwnership(address newOwner) public virtual onlyOwner {
        require(newOwner != address(0), "Ownable: new owner is the zero address");
        _transferOwnership(newOwner);
    }
```

This fixes the problem, however, certain functions will no longer be accessible, since they do not exist in the TraitForgeNFT contract.

i. allowedCaller cannot be updated going [against protocol intention](https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/279b2887e3d38bc219a05d332cbcb0655b2dc644/contracts/EntropyGenerator/EntropyGenerator.sol#L35);

ii. If the TraitForgeNft.sol contract in use gets retired for another, the ownership cannot be [transferred](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/fd81a96f01cc42ef1c9a5399364968d0e07e9e90/contracts/access/Ownable.sol#L69);

iii. Potentially pausing (absent funtion but another issue) EntropyGenerator.sol in case of an emergency will be impossible as the function will most likely be protected by the owner, and the function to pause EntropyGenerator.sol is also absent from the TraitForgeNFT.sol.

Although not in scope, the same issues can be found in functions related to [Airdrop.sol](https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/279b2887e3d38bc219a05d332cbcb0655b2dc644/contracts/Airdrop/Airdrop.sol#L20C1-L74C4) in TraitForgeNft.sol as if after starting airdrop and allowing DAO fund, there will be no way to pause claims in case of an [emergency](https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/279b2887e3d38bc219a05d332cbcb0655b2dc644/contracts/Airdrop/Airdrop.sol#L67) since the function to do so is missing in TraitForgeNFT.sol


### Tools Used
Manual code review

### Recommended Mitigation Steps
Recommendation is to fix the `onlyAllowedCaller` by allowing either the contract owner or the allowedCaller to be able to call it. This fixes calling the function during deployment.

```diff
  modifier onlyAllowedCaller() {
-    require(msg.sender == allowedCaller, 'Caller is not allowed');
+    require(msg.sender == allowedCaller || msg.sender == owner(), 'Caller is not allowed');
    _;
  }
```

Alternatively, rewriting the contracts to ensure that TraitForgeNFT.sol's owner performs the needed deployments and also introducing functions to access other owner functions in these contracts, or just checking that the caller is the owner or nftcontract.


