# `TraitForgeNft` is only able to `mint generation 1` due to wrong access control

# Lines of code

https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/main/contracts/TraitForgeNft/TraitForgeNft.sol#L353
https://github.com/code-423n4/2024-07-traitforge/blob/main/contracts/EntropyGenerator/EntropyGenerator.sol#L206


# Vulnerability details

## Description
There is a bug in `TraitForgeNft` which break `_incrementGeneration` and will make it always revert when trying to mint generation 2 as missing proper access control which seems to warrant `High` severity.

The root cause is due to the fact that `_incrementGeneration` is calling `EntropyGenerator::initializeAlphaIndices` which is assuming that TraitForgeNft is it's owner, but it is not. The problem is actually the onlyOwner modifier, `onlyAllowedCaller` should also be able to access this function, but in the end it require both (because of the call in the contructor).


```solidity
  function _incrementGeneration() private {
    require(
      generationMintCounts[currentGeneration] >= maxTokensPerGen,
      'Generation limit not yet reached'
    );
    currentGeneration++;
    generationMintCounts[currentGeneration] = 0;
    priceIncrement = priceIncrement + priceIncrementByGen;
    entropyGenerator.initializeAlphaIndices();  // <-----------------------------
    emit GenerationIncremented(currentGeneration);
  }
```  

```solidity
  function initializeAlphaIndices() public whenNotPaused onlyOwner { // <----------------------------- onlyOwner modifier make the call revert when trying to increment to gen2
    uint256 hashValue = uint256(
      keccak256(abi.encodePacked(blockhash(block.number - 1), block.timestamp))
    );

    uint256 slotIndexSelection = (hashValue % 258) + 512;
    uint256 numberIndexSelection = hashValue % 13;

    slotIndexSelectionPoint = slotIndexSelection;
    numberIndexSelectionPoint = numberIndexSelection;
  }
```  

## Impact
Game will be deployed/started without any problem. The problem will arise when players try to mint generation 2, `the minting or forging will always revert` at that point, which will cause an headache for the dev team as they would need to migrate the actual game to a new contract, which will be very annoying. 

The High severity here is justified by the fact that this would be only discovered after day(s) (until gen1 is fully minted), and players will have money locked already in the contract, and since this contract is not upgradable, it will be a painfull endeavor. Imagine having everything pump-up for the game launch, investing in audits, marketing, etc, but a core element of the game stop working once generation 1 is all minted (due to the competition, that might go actually fast, it would still be a major issue).

